This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it focuses on natural language understanding and dialogue management. It also involves the use of APIs and data sources to expand knowledge bases, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the challenges faced by an open domain socialbot, which could be categorized under cs.SD (Software Engineering) or cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper mentions the use of scoring mechanisms, which could be related to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
